# Project Structure and Entry Points

- Source code lives under [`src`](mdc:src)
- Main processing module: [`src/engine.py`](mdc:src/engine.py)
- CLI entry point: [`src/main.py`](mdc:src/main.py)
- Unit tests under [`tests`](mdc:tests)
- Dependencies in [`requirements.txt`](mdc:requirements.txt)

The engine reads `drivers.csv` and `rides.csv`, validates records, detects anomalies (high fare > 500, rapid rides defined as more than 2 rides within a 2-minute window per driver), aggregates driver performance, and writes:
- `driver_performance.csv`
- `anomaly_report.csv`

Run the end-to-end job via:
```bash
python -m src.main --drivers drivers.csv --rides rides.csv --outdir .
```
